node.text: "Art is the easiest way to reflect your personal style in your home," says prop-and-interior stylist Jonathan Thornton. node.text: “My artistic ethos would be community, conversation, [and] dialogue," says illustrator, visual artist, and creative behind our latest collab  @lukejohnmatthewarnold. Step inside his vibrant, art-filled studio to learn more about his process (and his trusty sidekick, Berry). 🎨🐾

node.text: “I love to touch different kinds of art[s] and crafts. I like to sew, I like to knit, I like to paint, to do ceramics," says French artist @nathalie_lete of her ever-inspired creative process. "In my work I try to put all of my feelings inside. I, myself, am like a big kid in my soul.” Here, she welcomes us inside her eclectic Paris studio, where whimsical vignettes and vintage treasures delight and inspire 🎨🌷🍄

node.title: The Artist's Studio with Nathalie Leté
